  "body": "Currently, geth implements [EIP-3607](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3607) (a.k.a. reject transactions from senders with deployed code) as [follows](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/state_transition.go#L283-L288):\r\n\r\n```go\r\n// Make sure the sender is an EOA\r\ncodeHash := st.state.GetCodeHash(msg.From)\r\nif codeHash != (common.Hash{}) && codeHash != types.EmptyCodeHash {\r\n\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: address %v, codehash: %s\", ErrSenderNoEOA,\r\n\t\tmsg.From.Hex(), codeHash)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm having a hard time in understanding why `codeHash` is checked against the zero hash `common.Hash` as this is not required by EIP-3607. Can you maybe enlighten me ðŸ˜„?",
